This paper is about a toolkit for neural sequence labeling, which is a task commonly studied in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also mentions that the toolkit is built on PyTorch, a popular deep learning framework, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the mention of state-of-the-art models such as LSTM-CRF suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), where sequence labeling is used for tasks such as object recognition and tracking.
